and her husband were there.

539
00:29:57,612 --> 00:29:58,863
I knew there was something
wrong when they painted

540
00:29:58,906 --> 00:29:59,866
that barn blue.

541
00:30:02,787 --> 00:30:03,747
[gasps] There's Theresa.

542
00:30:05,667 --> 00:30:06,543
Thank you.

543
00:30:06,586 --> 00:30:12,554
[quiet solemn music]

544
00:30:21,570 --> 00:30:23,239
- Keep moving.
- Don't force me.

545
00:30:24,450 --> 00:30:26,286
[yells] Don't force me!

546
00:30:26,328 --> 00:30:28,749
[gasping, chatter from crowd]

547
00:30:28,790 --> 00:30:31,337
[pattering feet]

548
00:30:33,173 --> 00:30:34,008
[door clicks shut]

549
00:30:34,050 --> 00:30:36,346
[chatter quiets down to lull]

550
00:30:39,226 --> 00:30:43,023
♪

551
00:30:51,038 --> 00:30:56,965
♪

552
00:31:04,060 --> 00:31:05,229
[gravel turning]

553
00:31:18,627 --> 00:31:25,306
♪

554
00:31:28,352 --> 00:31:30,398
[Emma] Will it
ever happen to us?

555
00:31:31,775 --> 00:31:32,610
No.

556
00:31:34,238 --> 00:31:35,907
Not until you're very old.

557
00:31:38,746 --> 00:31:40,832
[feet running down hallway]

558
00:31:40,874 --> 00:31:46,050
♪

559
00:31:52,603 --> 00:31:54,856
[t.v.] You really do
take him everywhere!

560
00:31:54,899 --> 00:31:56,568
[woman on t.v. laughs]
[kitchen appliances rattle]

561
00:31:56,610 --> 00:31:58,154
I'm not sure
I should leave you.

562
00:31:58,822 --> 00:31:59,949
Ah, we'll be fine, Mom.

563
00:31:59,990 --> 00:32:01,952
[t.v. chatter in background]

564
00:32:01,994 --> 00:32:03,914
I could call them tonight
and tell them that...

565
00:32:03,956 --> 00:32:05,626
We'll miss you,
but we'll get along.

566
00:32:06,419 --> 00:32:07,670
Besides, they're
counting on you.

567
00:32:09,090 --> 00:32:10,342
[t.v. in background]

568
00:32:11,636 --> 00:32:13,472
[foot steps approach]
Oh, look who's up!

569
00:32:14,140 --> 00:32:16,310
You should go.

570
00:32:16,352 --> 00:32:17,939
Where are you going,
Grandma?

571
00:32:19,149 --> 00:32:20,986
Oh, well I'm going
to take care of some

572
00:32:21,027 --> 00:32:24,533
babies that are
less fortunate than you.

573
00:32:25,368 --> 00:32:28,290
[t.v. chatter, clicks off]
Hey! Turn that back on!

574
00:32:28,332 --> 00:32:29,333
On!

575
00:32:29,375 --> 00:32:31,212
[Claire] On!
[Emma] I hate you mom!

576
00:32:31,546 --> 00:32:32,839
I hate you!

577
00:32:32,881 --> 00:32:35,552
Emma, lamb, don't speak
to your mother like that.

578
00:32:35,594 --> 00:32:36,554
[sighs]

579
00:32:41,146 --> 00:32:43,692
[rustling, dishes clatter]

580
00:32:47,072 --> 00:32:48,700
Okay, girls.

581
00:32:49,493 --> 00:32:51,121
Let's go for a ride, okay?
Come on. [grunts]

582
00:32:51,163 --> 00:32:53,500
[girls giggle]
[Claire] I want that!

583
00:32:53,542 --> 00:32:54,919
[Claire] I want som-
We'll get another one!

584
00:32:56,463 --> 00:32:57,507
[Emma] Where are we going?

585
00:32:58,676 --> 00:33:00,972
[paper rustles]

586
00:33:03,059 --> 00:33:05,813
Alice, dear. I, I, I can't help
but worry about you.

587
00:33:07,316 --> 00:33:08,693
You just need to...

588
00:33:09,361 --> 00:33:11,114
...be more positive.

589
00:33:11,156 --> 00:33:13,410
And not think such
dark thoughts.

590
00:33:13,452 --> 00:33:16,039
[crickets chirping]

591
00:33:20,965 --> 00:33:22,425
I need some air.

592
00:33:26,140 --> 00:33:30,439
[floor creaks,
door hingen squeaks]

593
00:33:31,358 --> 00:33:32,902
[loud clacking of wood]

594
00:33:36,867 --> 00:33:38,745
[crickets grow louder]

595
00:33:45,132 --> 00:33:48,220
[woman sobbing in distance]

596
00:33:57,695 --> 00:34:00,449
[crickets and cicadas]

597
00:34:02,745 --> 00:34:03,998
[sobbing]

598
00:34:12,721 --> 00:34:17,813
[sobbing continues]

599
00:34:21,528 --> 00:34:24,700
[crying grows louder]

600
00:34:28,582 --> 00:34:29,667
[sobbing]
Theresa?

601
00:34:29,709 --> 00:34:33,215
[sobbing, panting]
You scared me.

602
00:34:33,256 --> 00:34:35,427
[panting, catching breath]
I'm sorry...

603
00:34:35,469 --> 00:34:38,432
Don't! [pants, gasping for air]

604
00:34:38,474 --> 00:34:40,269
[sniffling]

605
00:34:41,187 --> 00:34:42,272
[gasps]

606
00:34:44,652 --> 00:34:47,239
[sniffling, lighter clicks]
I know.

607
00:34:47,281 --> 00:34:49,076
But it's helping right now.

608
00:34:51,163 --> 00:34:53,750
- I didn't...
- Don't.

609
00:34:54,669 --> 00:34:56,463
[sniffles]
There's nothing to say.

610
00:34:57,758 --> 00:34:59,009
That's a terrible thing.

611
00:35:02,725 --> 00:35:05,020
It's hard for me
to see you right now.

612
00:35:05,062 --> 00:35:05,772
I know.

613
00:35:07,858 --> 00:35:09,193
No, you don't know.
[voice cracking]

614
00:35:09,236 --> 00:35:11,949
[sobbing]

615
00:35:11,990 --> 00:35:13,243
[moaning]

616
00:35:14,161 --> 00:35:16,832
[sobbing loudly]
Oh! It's amazing how much

617
00:35:16,873 --> 00:35:18,043
a person can cry.

618
00:35:18,669 --> 00:35:20,505
[sniffles] You know, I...

619
00:35:20,547 --> 00:35:23,427
I decided to write down
all the things I...

620
00:35:23,469 --> 00:35:24,929
...I could remember
about her.

621
00:35:25,723 --> 00:35:27,559
I was terrified
there wasn't much.

622
00:35:27,601 --> 00:35:28,352
[sharp exhale]

623
00:35:28,393 --> 00:35:29,396
But I started...

624
00:35:30,815 --> 00:35:35,030
...right at conception,
and... God. It all came back.

625
00:35:35,990 --> 00:35:37,201
Every doctor's visit.

626
00:35:37,952 --> 00:35:40,248
Hearing her heartbeat
on the stethoscope thing.

627
00:35:41,333 --> 00:35:42,793
[crying] The birth...

628
00:35:42,836 --> 00:35:44,463
Her first tooth.

629
00:35:44,505 --> 00:35:47,218
[crying, sniffling]

630
00:35:47,260 --> 00:35:49,513
Everyone says,
you know...

631
00:35:49,556 --> 00:35:52,060
"Go on with your life,
keep busy, plant a garden,

632
00:35:52,102 --> 00:35:53,103
take a vacation."

633
00:35:54,105 --> 00:35:55,900
My sister thinks
I should get a puppy.

634
00:35:57,110 --> 00:35:59,907
And Dan still gets up
at 4o'clock every morning...

635
00:35:59,949 --> 00:36:01,743
...work, work, work,
like nothing's happened.

636
00:36:01,785 --> 00:36:04,248
And Audrey, well, she's doing
the best of all of us.

637
00:36:05,125 --> 00:36:06,335
She's running around shouting

638
00:36:06,376 --> 00:36:08,547
"My sister's in heaven!
My sister's in heaven!"

639
00:36:08,589 --> 00:36:10,133
[sniffles] Me, you know...

640
00:36:11,385 --> 00:36:12,303
[puffs cigarette]

641
00:36:12,345 --> 00:36:13,305
I eat, I shower.

642
00:36:14,558 --> 00:36:16,728
I'm afraid to leave
cause I keep thinking...

643
00:36:17,521 --> 00:36:20,276
...maybe Lizzy
will come back. [sobs]

644
00:36:20,318 --> 00:36:22,112
And we won't be home.
[voice cracking]

645
00:36:22,153 --> 00:36:24,950
[crickets and cicadas]

646
00:36:24,992 --> 00:36:26,620
[sniffles]

647
00:36:26,662 --> 00:36:28,749
[owl hoots in forest]

648
00:36:28,790 --> 00:36:30,085
Where are you going?

649
00:36:30,126 --> 00:36:31,629
Well, we thought Cape Cod
but now we're thinking

650
00:36:31,670 --> 00:36:33,841
the Grand Canyon.
I don't want to go.

651
00:36:33,882 --> 00:36:34,718
Theresa?

652
00:36:37,138 --> 00:36:38,599
I know you're sorry, Alice.

653
00:36:39,768 --> 00:36:41,353
I'm even sorry you're sorry.

654
00:36:42,481 --> 00:36:44,401
But that doesn't
do me any good right now.

655
00:36:44,442 --> 00:36:46,696
[crickets, cicadas, owl hoots]

656
00:36:46,738 --> 00:36:48,616
Don't ever tell Dan
I smoked, okay?

657
00:36:54,878 --> 00:36:56,546
[door closes]
Bye Gramma!

658
00:36:56,589 --> 00:36:57,882
[Claire] Bye Gramma!

659
00:36:57,925 --> 00:37:00,596
[feet patter]

660
00:37:00,638 --> 00:37:02,098
[both] Bye Gran!

661
00:37:02,473 --> 00:37:03,768
[gravel scraping]
[Emma] Bye!

662
00:37:05,229 --> 00:37:06,146
Okay, come on.

663
00:37:06,189 --> 00:37:07,733
Let's get up.
[pat, pat, pat]

664
00:37:08,902 --> 00:37:10,529
Come on, come on,
come on. Let's go.

665
00:37:10,571 --> 00:37:11,281
Stop it.

666
00:37:14,202 --> 00:37:15,913
You know,
I know you Alice.

667
00:37:16,832 --> 00:37:18,961
Someday you're gonna
turn this into a story.

668
00:37:19,586 --> 00:37:21,465
[sighs] You're gonna tell
a bunch of dinner guests

669
00:37:21,506 --> 00:37:22,466
about the time you were
so depressed,

670
00:37:22,509 --> 00:37:24,262
I had to dress you myself.

671
00:37:25,765 --> 00:37:27,726
You're gonna say something
about how I had to

672
00:37:27,768 --> 00:37:30,063
dust off your feet to put on
your socks. Come on.

673
00:37:30,105 --> 00:37:32,609
[panting, rustling]
Come on. Look alive.

674
00:37:32,651 --> 00:37:33,862
I can't!

675
00:37:35,322 --> 00:37:36,282
Okay.

676
00:37:36,325 --> 00:37:38,411
[groans] Come on,
come on. Up! Up.

677
00:37:38,453 --> 00:37:39,746
Up, up, up!
[Alice panting]

678
00:37:39,789 --> 00:37:41,041
Claire misses you.

679
00:37:42,168 --> 00:37:43,670
And Emma is in a mood.

680
00:37:43,712 --> 00:37:44,798
Please.

681
00:37:45,465 --> 00:37:47,469
There's a school board
meeting tonight.

682
00:37:47,510 --> 00:37:49,055
They're discussing contracts.

683
00:37:49,096 --> 00:37:50,808
- You should go.
- No!

684
00:37:51,768 --> 00:37:53,312
We can't change
what happened.

685
00:37:54,313 --> 00:37:55,149
No one blames you.

686
00:37:56,025 --> 00:37:56,860
You know that.

687
00:37:58,488 --> 00:38:00,408
We have to get on with things.

688
00:38:00,449 --> 00:38:01,451
[sighs]

689
00:38:02,786 --> 00:38:04,081
Now, come on.

690
00:38:05,625 --> 00:38:07,128
You know, I hear you,
and I-

691
00:38:07,169 --> 00:38:10,049
I understand exactly what
it is you're trying to tell me,

692
00:38:10,091 --> 00:38:13,555
but... you know, [sighs]
we are in a bad position here.

693
00:38:13,598 --> 00:38:16,143
Even though our
community is...

694
00:38:16,185 --> 00:38:19,816
...is still growing, we are
faced with these massive

695
00:38:19,858 --> 00:38:21,235
budget restraints.

696
00:38:21,278 --> 00:38:23,072
And that's just the way
it is people, there's not

697
00:38:23,113 --> 00:38:24,700
a thing we can
do about that.

698
00:38:24,742 --> 00:38:27,246
So I'm gonna have to
ask you for your help here.

699
00:38:27,288 --> 00:38:29,208
- Hi.
- Okay? We have all

700
00:38:29,249 --> 00:38:31,962
got to consider carefully
the kinds of changes

701
00:38:32,005 --> 00:38:33,506
that we need to make.
I mean, whether it's to

702
00:38:33,549 --> 00:38:36,512
curriculum, or...
or staffing, or to the

703
00:38:36,553 --> 00:38:37,430
building itself...

704
00:38:37,472 --> 00:38:41,938
[faucet running]

705
00:38:42,481 --> 00:38:43,358
Mrs. Goodwin?

706
00:38:48,616 --> 00:38:51,162
I'm Detective Grogan from the
investigation unit in Racine.

707
00:38:51,205 --> 00:38:53,249
I'd like to talk to you
for a minute, if you don't mind.

708
00:38:53,291 --> 00:38:54,209
Me?

709
00:38:54,251 --> 00:38:55,211
Just for a minute.

710
00:38:55,253 --> 00:38:57,841
[sighs, paper rustles]

711
00:38:59,635 --> 00:39:01,222
[door creaks on hinges]

712
00:39:06,146 --> 00:39:07,106
[door clicks shut]

713
00:39:07,149 --> 00:39:08,401
This is Officer Melby.

714
00:39:09,069 --> 00:39:12,073
Welby? [chuckles]
As in Marcus Welby?

715
00:39:12,115 --> 00:39:13,785
[chortles]

716
00:39:13,826 --> 00:39:15,079
We're trying to get some
information about

717
00:39:15,121 --> 00:39:16,498
Robbie Mackessy.

718
00:39:16,539 --> 00:39:18,168
Oh God...

719
00:39:18,793 --> 00:39:20,213
Not pleasant memories
I take it?

720
00:39:21,298 --> 00:39:22,759
I think you could say.

721
00:39:22,801 --> 00:39:24,470
You have a relationship
with Robbie?

722
00:39:24,512 --> 00:39:26,432
Oh... pfft.

723
00:39:26,473 --> 00:39:28,435
- What's funny?
- Kids are usually

724
00:39:28,478 --> 00:39:30,230
afraid of the school nurse.

725
00:39:30,272 --> 00:39:31,482
Afraid?

726
00:39:31,524 --> 00:39:33,110
Yeah, I'm a tall person
who carries a needle.

727
00:39:33,152 --> 00:39:34,779
[woman chuckles]

728
00:39:35,990 --> 00:39:37,535
You know, I have to go.
- Oh, just...

729
00:39:37,576 --> 00:39:39,204
Just a few questions.
Please Mrs. Goodwin.

730
00:39:39,246 --> 00:39:41,416
The more we know about
Robbie, the better we can
assist him.

731
00:39:42,084 --> 00:39:44,379
Uh, what sort of trouble
is he in now?

732
00:39:45,465 --> 00:39:47,176
We're not able to
comment, I'm afraid.

733
00:39:47,218 --> 00:39:48,679
We wonder if you
remembered any

734
00:39:48,721 --> 00:39:50,599
strange behavioral
patterns?

735
00:39:50,641 --> 00:39:52,435
[laughs heartily] Oh well.

736
00:39:52,478 --> 00:39:55,065
His crazy mother always
brings him to school sick.

737
00:39:56,275 --> 00:39:58,029
What kind of sickness
did he have?

738
00:39:58,070 --> 00:39:59,615
Oh God, I mean,
you know,

739
00:39:59,656 --> 00:40:02,495
sore throats,
ear infections, you know,

740
00:40:02,536 --> 00:40:04,331
the common cold, you know,
you name it.

741
00:40:04,373 --> 00:40:06,752
- I, I have to go.
- Are you okay?

742
00:40:06,793 --> 00:40:09,048
Uh, [laughs lightly] no.
I- I'm not well.

743
00:40:09,089 --> 00:40:11,593
I'm sorry to keep you
standing. Why don't we sit?

744
00:40:11,635 --> 00:40:12,971
This really won't take
much longer.

745
00:40:13,013 --> 00:40:14,682
You see, I'm sick.

746
00:40:14,724 --> 00:40:16,226
And I really can't...

747
00:40:16,268 --> 00:40:18,439
We just have a few
more things to ask.

748
00:40:18,481 --> 00:40:19,649
[sniffles]

749
00:40:19,691 --> 00:40:21,778
[laughs, crying]
You want to know the truth?

750
00:40:21,819 --> 00:40:24,491
I am trying, [gasps]
to have a complete

751
00:40:24,533 --> 00:40:26,703
nervous breakdown,
and no one will let me

752
00:40:26,745 --> 00:40:28,665
do it in peace!

753
00:40:28,706 --> 00:40:29,666
[giggles]

754
00:40:29,708 --> 00:40:31,211
What's the matter?

755
00:40:31,253 --> 00:40:32,463
Mrs. Goodwin?

756
00:40:33,298 --> 00:40:36,178
- Mrs. Goodwin...
- I hurt everybody.

757
00:40:37,346 --> 00:40:40,268
[shoes squeaking,
patters down hall, crying]

758
00:40:42,272 --> 00:40:44,233
[door opens and shuts]

759
00:40:44,275 --> 00:40:45,945
[crickets chirping]

760
00:40:49,868 --> 00:40:51,872
- Hey.
- Hi.

761
00:40:53,458 --> 00:40:55,336
[sheets rustling]

762
00:40:55,378 --> 00:40:58,091
[sighs, groans]

763
00:41:02,139 --> 00:41:02,849
How'd it go?

764
00:41:03,684 --> 00:41:05,145
- Fine.
- Okay?

765
00:41:05,186 --> 00:41:06,146
Yeah.

766
00:41:14,912 --> 00:41:16,539
[bed creaking]
You alright?

767
00:41:16,582 --> 00:41:18,168
[scoffs] Yes.

768
00:41:19,753 --> 00:41:21,632
[smooches] Hi.

769
00:41:21,673 --> 00:41:22,801
Hi.

770
00:41:27,517 --> 00:41:29,479
[bed creaks, sigh]

771
00:41:29,521 --> 00:41:30,648
- What's the matter?
- Nothing.

772
00:41:32,317 --> 00:41:35,865
[sighs, sheets rustle]

773
00:41:37,868 --> 00:41:39,121
[sharp exhale]

774
00:41:39,997 --> 00:41:41,833
[sighs, deep breath]

775
00:41:43,044 --> 00:41:46,466
[bed creaks, both
breathing heavily]

776
00:41:46,508 --> 00:41:47,719
sniffles]

777
00:41:52,435 --> 00:41:53,729
[sharp exhales]

778
00:42:03,412 --> 00:42:04,665
[wooden bed frame
creaking, sheets rustle]

779
00:42:10,342 --> 00:42:11,552
Hey.
[sniffles]

780
00:42:11,593 --> 00:42:12,888
Hey. [smooch]

781
00:42:15,099 --> 00:42:16,519
Did you get a raise?

782
00:42:16,561 --> 00:42:18,146
[exasperated sigh]

783
00:42:39,099 --> 00:42:40,477
- Are you alright?
- Mm-hmmm.

784
00:42:43,315 --> 00:42:44,442
[chortles]

785
00:42:44,484 --> 00:42:47,698
[chuckle] Wha-
What's so funny?

786
00:42:49,952 --> 00:42:51,121
[groans]

787
00:42:51,162 --> 00:42:52,748
[sniffles]

788
00:42:54,626 --> 00:42:55,336
[groans]

789
00:42:56,421 --> 00:43:00,219
[panting, moaning]
You okay?

790
00:43:01,472 --> 00:43:04,519
[bed creaking, panting,
Alice laughing]

791
00:43:04,561 --> 00:43:05,479
Alice?

792
00:43:05,521 --> 00:43:07,983
- Yes?
- What?

793
00:43:08,025 --> 00:43:09,736
[bed thuds wall]
Come on...

794
00:43:09,778 --> 00:43:12,866
[panting]

795
00:43:12,908 --> 00:43:13,659
[Alice groans unhappily]

796
00:43:13,701 --> 00:43:16,039
[slaps, sheets rustling]

797
00:43:17,291 --> 00:43:19,378
[crying]

798
00:43:20,922 --> 00:43:22,425
[gasps, crying]

799
00:43:26,348 --> 00:43:29,896
[gasping for air]

800
00:43:31,816 --> 00:43:33,861
[loud bang]

801
00:43:34,529 --> 00:43:37,910
[foot steps approach]

802
00:43:37,952 --> 00:43:40,039
In case you hadn't
noticed, there's no food.

803
00:43:40,873 --> 00:43:42,168
[dishes clatter]

804
00:43:42,209 --> 00:43:44,338
[faucet running]

805
00:43:45,465 --> 00:43:47,385
[door clicks]
There's a list on the table.

806
00:43:50,473 --> 00:43:51,517
[can pops, fizz]

807
00:43:52,602 --> 00:43:54,731
[dishes clatter in sink]

808
00:43:57,235 --> 00:43:59,656
Congratulations
for getting up, by the way.

809
00:44:00,241 --> 00:44:02,077
No sweetheart.
No.

810
00:44:03,329 --> 00:44:04,665
[rattling]

811
00:44:04,706 --> 00:44:06,209
Keep in motion, Alice.

812
00:44:06,251 --> 00:44:08,713
For the sake of the kids,
just keep in motion.

813
00:44:08,755 --> 00:44:11,009
[Claire humming,
foot steps recede]

814
00:44:13,388 --> 00:44:14,641
Want a bite?

815
00:44:14,682 --> 00:44:18,105
[tractor hums loudly]

816
00:44:21,945 --> 00:44:23,989
[hinge squeaks]
Emma, get in the car.

817
00:44:27,746 --> 00:44:28,915
Get in the car!

818
00:44:31,252 --> 00:44:32,672
[yells] Get in the car!

819
00:44:36,428 --> 00:44:37,138
[door slams]

820
00:44:42,188 --> 00:44:43,399
[loud thud]

821
00:44:43,441 --> 00:44:46,321
[engine turns over]

822
00:44:47,572 --> 00:44:50,703
Oh, the list.
I forgot the goddamn list.

823
00:44:50,745 --> 00:44:51,705
Stay here!

824
00:44:53,666 --> 00:44:55,753
[mocking tone]
Motion, Alice. Keep in motion.

825
00:44:55,795 --> 00:44:58,968
[tractor engine whirs loudly]

826
00:44:59,009 --> 00:45:02,098
[birds chirping, gravel turns]

827
00:45:07,148 --> 00:45:11,322
[tractor engine roars]

828
00:45:11,364 --> 00:45:12,992
- Alice Goodwin?
- Yes.

829
00:45:13,033 --> 00:45:14,578
We have a warrant
for your arrest.

830
00:45:14,619 --> 00:45:16,706
- Charge of child abuse.
- What?

831
00:45:17,875 --> 00:45:21,715
[tractor humming]

832
00:45:22,383 --> 00:45:23,343
Just come with us, please.

833
00:45:25,221 --> 00:45:26,849
Right this way.
Towards the car.

834
00:45:26,891 --> 00:45:29,979
[engine humming]

835
00:45:30,939 --> 00:45:32,108
Put your hands
on the front of the car.

836
00:45:32,149 --> 00:45:33,109
Howard!

837
00:45:35,489 --> 00:45:36,699
Howard!

838
00:45:36,741 --> 00:45:38,411
You have the right
to an attorney,

839
00:45:38,452 --> 00:45:40,205
if you cannot afford one,
one will be appointed
by the courts.

840
00:45:40,248 --> 00:45:40,998
[Howard; yells] Alice!

841
00:45:41,875 --> 00:45:43,753
[pattering]
Alice?

842
00:45:43,795 --> 00:45:45,548
Howard!

843
00:45:45,589 --> 00:45:47,635
Robbie Mackessy says
I did awful things.

844
00:45:47,677 --> 00:45:48,762
What's going on?

845
00:45:48,804 --> 00:45:50,223
I'm in trouble, Howard.

846
00:45:50,265 --> 00:45:51,768
- Will someone please expl-
- Read the piece of paper.

847
00:45:51,809 --> 00:45:53,478
- Explain to me what's goin-
- Howard...

848
00:45:53,521 --> 00:45:55,148
What's this? I don't have time
to read this.

849
00:45:55,189 --> 00:45:56,568
What you need to do,

850
00:45:56,609 --> 00:45:58,654
what you need to do
is take care of the girls.

851
00:45:58,696 --> 00:46:00,491
I'll call as soon as
I sort this out.

852
00:46:00,532 --> 00:46:01,952
- Ma'am.
- No, please, giv-

853
00:46:01,993 --> 00:46:03,121
- Give me a minute!
- I'm going with you.

854
00:46:03,162 --> 00:46:04,915
- No! No Howard.
- Alice, I...

855
00:46:04,957 --> 00:46:06,334
Girls!

856
00:46:06,376 --> 00:46:07,545
Girls!

857
00:46:07,586 --> 00:46:08,672
Sir, why is she being
arrested, please...

858
00:46:08,713 --> 00:46:09,632
Oh, sweethearts,

859
00:46:09,673 --> 00:46:10,842
be good okay?

860
00:46:11,468 --> 00:46:12,595
[smooches]

861
